works.description:
I formally request that this entire  
submission to Google Inc, and it's subsidaries and third-parties, such as 

ChillingEffects do not have the right to public this content publicly.  
(Such as a publicly listed DCMA notice)

The work was originally a series of photos in a  Public Listed Google  
Picasa Album.

The copyrighted works included partially erotic photographs which were  
in-advertedly uploaded into my public album.

Previous attempts at removing them and trying to use the URL removal tool 

have failed to remove the images from Google Image Search. Even though
they  
are no longer in Picasa.

Searching, "Cady Oldfield" in Google Image Search reveals ALL the photos
in  
the second to around 8th image.

The fact that these images are STILL appearing and in such a easy to find 

manner is disturbing. This is a unacceptable breach of my copyright. I
hope  
you can aid me in resolving this issue as soon as possible.
